ciscoPropAtmIfMIB.name: ciscoPropAtmIfMIB

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoPropAtmIfMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-voice-gateway@cisco.com
ciscoPropAtmIfMIB.description: This MIB is designed for Propietary ATM (propAtm) interfaces. The propAtm interfaces are identified in the ifTable entries with ifType 197 (as defined in IANAifType-MIB). This interface is a switch virtual interface which does not have any physical connector(jack).

cpAtmIfConfigTable.name: cpAtmIfConfigTable
cpAtmIfConfigTable.description: This table is used to configure propAtm interfaces. Each entry in this table has a corresponding ifTable entry with ifType propAtm(197). The ifIndex value of that associated ifTable entry is used to index this this table. The entry of this table is added after its associated ifEntry is added in the ifTable of IF-MIB. It is impossible to add/delete entry to/from this table.

cpAtmIfConfigEntry.name: cpAtmIfConfigEntry
cpAtmIfConfigEntry.description: An entry in the cpAtmIfConfigTable table for each propAtm port interface. .

cpAtmIfMaxBandwidth.name: cpAtmIfMaxBandwidth
cpAtmIfMaxBandwidth.description: The propATM interface's maximum cell rate.

cpAtmIfStatsEgressTable.name: cpAtmIfStatsEgressTable
cpAtmIfStatsEgressTable.description: This table reflects real-time statistics associated with each of propAtm interfaces on the egress side. Ingress terminology is used for the cells that are generated by the voice gateway on the TDM side and are going toward the ATM switch. Egress terminology means the cells that are coming from the ATM switch into the TDM side. This table contains statistics from this egress point of view.

cpAtmIfStatsEgressEntry.name: cpAtmIfStatsEgressEntry
cpAtmIfStatsEgressEntry.description: An entry in the cpAtmIfStatsEgressTable table for each propAtm port interface. CLP-0 means Cell Loss Priority = 0, CLP-1 means Cell Loss Priority = 1.

cpAtmIfEgrRcvClp1Cells.name: cpAtmIfEgrRcvClp1Cells

cpAtmIfEgressIntervalTable.name: cpAtmIfEgressIntervalTable
cpAtmIfEgressIntervalTable.description: This table reflects interval(each 15 minute) statistics associated witheach of the propAtm interfaces on egress side.

cpAtmIfEgressIntervalEntry.name: cpAtmIfEgressIntervalEntry
cpAtmIfEgressIntervalEntry.description: An entry in the cpAtmIfEgressIntervalTable table for each propAtm port interface. CLP-0 means Cell Loss Priority = 0, CLP-1 means Cell Loss Priority = 1.

cpAtmIfEgressIntervalNumber.name: cpAtmIfEgressIntervalNumber
cpAtmIfEgressIntervalNumber.description: Index of the table which represents the interval number. An interval number between 1 and 96, where 1 is the most recently completed 15 minute interval and 96 is the 15 minutes interval completed 23 hours an 45 minutes prior to interval 1.
